### ECOMMERCE API TEST REQUESTS ###

# Base URL Configuration
@baseUrl = https://localhost:5001
# If using HTTP instead of HTTPS:
# @baseUrl = http://localhost:5000

# JWT Token storage
@token = {{login.response.body.token}}

## ==================== AUTHENTICATION ====================

### Register a new user
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "Password123",
  "name": "John Doe"
}

### Login and get JWT token
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "Password123"
}

## ==================== PRODUCTS ====================

### Get all products (public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products
Accept: application/json

### Get product by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/1
Accept: application/json

### Create product (Admin only - requires token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "iPhone 15 Pro",
  "description": "Latest iPhone with A17 Pro chip",
  "price": 999.99,
  "categoryId": 1,
  "brand": "Apple",
  "stock": 50,
  "specifications": "{\"display\":\"6.1-inch\",\"ram\":\"8GB\",\"storage\":\"256GB\"}"
}

## ==================== PRODUCT COMPARISON ====================

### Compare two products
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/comparison/compare
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "product1Id": 1,
  "product2Id": 2
}

### Get comparison history
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/comparison/history
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

## ==================== TEST ENDPOINTS ====================

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Accept: application/json

### Swagger UI
GET {{baseUrl}}/swagger
Accept: text/html

### Swagger JSON
GET {{baseUrl}}/swagger/v1/swagger.json
Accept: application/json

### Simple test endpoint
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/test
Accept: application/json